http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/bangalore/CID-probe-into-alleged-ad-scam-in-BBMP/article14023136.ece

The Criminal Investigation Department (CID) will investigate the alleged scam in the advertisement wing of the Bruhat Bangalore Mahanagara Palike (BBMP).Following directions from the Governor’s office, the State government on January 22 decided to hand over the probe into the alleged Rs. 2,000 crore scam to the CID, which has been directed to submit a report at the earliest.It has been alleged that the civic body has incurred a loss of around Rs. 2,000 crore over the past eight years due to unauthorised hoardings mushrooming across the city, apart from failure of the BBMP officials to collect advertisement tax.BBMP’s assistant commissioner (advertisement) K. Mathai, in his reports, had blamed civic officials for the revenue leakage.